HEADWORD: Ineludible
<hw>In`e*lud"i*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Incapable of
being eluded or evaded; unvoidable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Most pressing reasons and <qex>ineludible</qex>
demonstrations.</q> <rj><qau>Glanvill.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

